  "prompt": "Which breeds of dog look like the Ewoks from Star Wars?",
  "response": "Ewoks, the small, bear-like creatures from Star Wars, have a few dog breeds that share some physical similarities. Here are some breeds that often resemble Ewoks:\n\n1. **Wheaten Terrier (Soft Coated Wheaten Terrier)**: This breed has a soft, fluffy coat and a friendly disposition, reminiscent of Ewoks.\n\n2. **Pekingese**: With their round faces and long, flowing fur, Pekingese dogs have a distinctly Ewok-like appearance.\n\n3. **Shih Tzu**: These small dogs have a playful personality and a fluffy coat that can also give them an Ewok-like look.\n\n4. **Pomeranian**: Their fluffy fur and small stature create a resemblance to the furry little creatures of Endor.\n\n5. **Lhasa Apso**: Similar to the Shih Tzu, Lhasa Apsos also have long fur and a compact size that can evoke the look of Ewoks.\n\nWhile no dog breed can perfectly replicate the unique design of an Ewok, these breeds share some resemblance in terms of size, fluffiness, and overall cuteness.",
